              <span class="timeline-desc">Humans memorized syntax. Exact commands, exact order, exact grammar. Powerful, unforgiving, unlimited &mdash; if you spoke the dialect. <em>The interface was a translation layer; the user paid the cost.</em></span>
              <span class="timeline-tag">Syntax &middot; Composability &middot; Expert-Only</span>
            </div>
          </a>

          <a href="#old-contract" class="timeline-item">
            <span class="timeline-year">1980s</span>
            <span class="timeline-dot"></span>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <span class="timeline-era">The GUI Era</span>
              <span class="timeline-desc">Spatial memory replaced syntax memory. Folders, windows, drag-and-drop. Friendly, accessible, bounded by what the designer anticipated. <em>The cost moved from grammar to geography &mdash; but stayed on the human.</em></span>
              <span class="timeline-tag">WIMP &middot; Spatial Memory &middot; Anticipated Paths</span>
            </div>
          </a>

          <a href="#old-contract" class="timeline-item">
            <span class="timeline-year">2010s</span>
            <span class="timeline-dot"></span>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <span class="timeline-era">Enterprise Bloat</span>
              <span class="timeline-desc">ERPs, CRMs, HRMS. Weeks of training. Certifications. Manuals. Institutional knowledge was often just <em>knowing which screen held which field in which module.</em> The cost compounded.</span>
              <span class="timeline-tag">SAP &middot; Salesforce &middot; Training-Heavy &middot; Module-Bound</span>
            </div>
          </a>

          <a href="#rupture" class="timeline-item timeline-item--active">
            <span class="timeline-year">2024+</span>
            <span class="timeline-dot"></span>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <span class="timeline-era">The Inversion</span>
              <span class="timeline-desc">The system translates the user's grammar into intent. Spatial memory becomes worthless. Articulation becomes the scarce skill. Knowledge bases become markdown the agent reads. Domain models become tools the LLM composes. <em>The translation layer moved to the machine side. The wall is broken.</em></span>
              <span class="timeline-tag">LLMs &middot; MCP &middot; Function Calling &middot; Articulation</span>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- ── AGENT SIDEBAR (sticky on desktop, stacks on tablet/mobile) ── -->
